om marinade, gently pat chicken dry with a paper towel and reserve the marinade. Add 2 tsp oil to skillet, place chicken in hot skillet skin side down and sear until browned (approx. 3-5 min. per side). Set aside and keep warm. Meanwhile make the Coq au Vin."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Coq au Vin"},{"content":"Place bacon and dried porcini mushrooms into mixing bowl and chop <b>6 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Without measuring cup sauté <b>20 min\/250°F\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add carrots and olive oil and without measuring cup cook <b>5 min\/250°F\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved marinade, pearl onions, fresh cremini mushrooms, flour and thyme and without measuring cup cook <b>10 min\/212°F\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add reserved seared chicken thighs and juices and without measuring cup cook a further <b>10-13 min\/195°F\/\/speed <b>, until chicken is cooked through. Remove bay leaf. Divide mixture between two bowls, garnish with additional thyme leaves and serve hot with fresh baguette."}],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h 40m","2 portions"]}